caption: This is GERMAN and I love beer! Best place to enjoy your loud family which I have. Plus we always makes friends with our table mates. Get the potato pancakes!!
Fresh, organic and honest ingredients prepared with soul.  Highly recommend.
(Translated by Google) Italian Parma ham with avocado sandwich!  (Original) Italian prosciutto di Parma with avocado sandwich!
Absolutely delicious!!! Offering 10% off if they have the board outside
Great german quality pretzel! Hard to find in the US, but this is one of these places.
Staff were super slow and it felt like it was their first day. The bun was hard and hurt my teeth and this hemp drink was $8 and tasted like snake oil.

The people working here are SO SO NICE and friendly and genuinely seem happy. I rarely see this when I get food from anywhere so I value it a lot. Gives me good vibes and makes me want to return just for that.  Now to the actual sandwich, it was created with care and it was delicious!! Fresh veggies, yummy turkey and great soup. Thank you!
Awesome Thanksgiving sandwich!! They have gf options too
Meh... Unfriendly staff and an odd menu

(Translated by Google) 100% recommendable. Not only for the quality of the products (they were delicious), but also for the quality of the treatment. Your dependents have been most pleasant. Without a doubt, to repeat. Super ecofriendly. 💜  (Original) 100% recomendable. No solamente por la calidad de los productos (estaban riquísimos), sino también por la calidad en el trato. Sus dependientes han sido de lo más agradables. Sin duda alguna, para repetir. Súper ecofriendly. 💜
(Translated by Google) For a small craving or simply visit the place ... To see  (Original) Pour une petite fringale ou simplement visiter le lieux... À voir
Just wished the sandwiches were a bit bigger but the flavor is great

I have a gluten allergy and this is the best gluten free sandwich I have ever had! The homemade bread is not crumbly, like most gf bread is, and it has flavor! The ingredients are fresh and I love the environmental consciousness of the entire company. HIGHLY recommend!!

Substance is back!  The BAGUETTE may be a better value, but the WECKEN is a smaller portion & great if you are not-that hungry.  Excellent savory breakfast pricing!  $5-ish on a Wecken.  In a word of fake meals, at least here, we know it's REAL!

Wow.  I walked in and was only person in store.  Now I understand why the store was empty.  There were at least 3 employees.  The one employee at the register walked into the back as I approached the register.  Then he stayed in back and chatted with another employee while I waited.  Then when he came back he had an attitude like I was inconveniencing him.  I don't think this Hannah's Bretzels will be there in the future.
Great fresh sandwiches, pretzels, and chocolate. Hofbrauhaus beer as well!
Friendly staff...Prosciutto/Avocado sandwich was outstanding...Delicious coffee...Clean and comfortable dining area, and, a whole aisle of chocolate bars and other chocolate specialties.
Not too bad, but not good!
Made roast beef when ordered salmon and then remade not on gluten free bread and I died.

Food is delicious and clearly of high quality. Portions are a little small given the prices, but the organic/food quality/eco-friendliness of it all explains the difference. Staff has always been friendly and accommodating. If you're vegan, try the Veggie Monster sandwich and the Avocado Pea soup.  Management: I would love to see a simple avocado toast on the menu for plant-based customers!
Quick and tasty
Great sandwiches! Love the pretzel buns. Their tea and chocolate selection is also drool-worthy.
Great spot.  One of my absolute favorite sandwich places.  Good chocolate chip cookies too!
Good food

What's better than combining the 2 best things in life: pretzel + bread = amazing concoction Bretzel. The soft doughy pretzel baguette and wecken roll are divine. I couldn't decide and glad I got both!  The Seasonal Angry Tofu on bretzel baquette was fun to try with a spicy kick from the Harissa sauce and the marinated tofu in a pepperjack hot sauce. Avocado, mixed greens, and tomatoes balanced out the flavor. The baguette was filling with little room to spare. You can get 1/2 portion on the wecken roll.  The savory and sweet combination of the Wecken roll and preserves hits the spot! I was skeptical, but glad my hubby ordered it!  Will definitely come back for more Bretzel! Wish there were locations on the East Coast, please open up a store in DC!
Food is great. Bread is fantastic.
The food delicious in this delicate way. And it’s a lovely place to be in.
Better tasting than expected.
Food
freshly made breakfast salad and sandwiches. clean roomy dining area with fast friendly staffs. enjoy their  nice  meals outside sitting area on a nice days
I thought the meal was ok. I had the salmon cream cheese sandwich. Service was a little slow and confusing.  They double charged me for the sandwich so make sure to double check your receipt.
Love breakfast and lunch sandwiches.  Organic is worth it, and the taste is above average for comparable venues.  Love the design and positive vibe.
Overpriced and underwhelming. Food isnt high enough quality to justify the price and the quantity isn't enough to justify the price.
Get the works breakfast sandwich. Only concern is price, everything tastes amazing.
Nice people. Great sandwich!
Excellent,  organic sandwiches.  Would eat there again.
Sandwiches were delicious but they are small and expensive for the size

I love the pretzel bread and their freshly baked organic bretzel baguettes are just so good. I am a classic turkey Hannah's Club kind of guy. I have tried most of their foodie sandwiches that are more complex and they are delicious of course. I like how eco friendly and focused they are as well. It is admirable and a good benchmark for others to start following. They also have a great chocolate selection that you won't find in other places.
It's a bit pricey but the sandwiches are worth it, great sandwiches and according to them they're organic.

(Translated by Google) Very good restaurant with friendly service. Unfortunately, only a little biological food.  (Original) Ganz gutes Lokal mit freundlicher Bedienung. Leider nur wenig biologische Speisen.

The gluten free baguette option for sandwiches is criminally dry and rock-hard. It's the kind of gf bread that makes people with celiac want to run and hide, which is a shame because there are a number of bakeries in/near the city that make and distribute wonderfully soft and delicious bread. The sandwich ingredients are quality and the tomato soup is good (make sure to tell them no croutons) but I'm not sure I've ever had worse gf bread in my life and I never want to eat it again.
It's tasty and fresh, but can't help feeling ripped off price wise.
The sandwiches are amazing, plus they have all kinds of quality chocolate.
Great food
It was a nice quiet getaway to have a nice meal. My food was well crafted and of great quality. The service was quick and efficient.

Great sandwiches and salads served in a warm modern ambiance. The pretzel buns add a great flavor and texture to the sandwiches. The salads are fresh,  reasonably priced and delicious. The owner is also a big chocolate fan so make sure to check the crazy selection of chocolates at the store.
Good
Now my favorite go to in Chicago for a quick bite
One of the best sandwich options in the city, love the club, also a crazy selection of chocolates.
The to-go containers, specifically the salad container has dramatically reduced in size. Additionally, I had the pea soup today and it was incredibly bland and flavorless that I had to throw it away.

Great pretzel rolls but I wish they were a little larger for the price.  I don't think a full sandwich would be filling for someone who was very hungry.  But very tasty ingredients.  I had a turkey sandwich with melted mozzarella and tomato sauce.
amazing pretzel sandwich makers; Having organic ingredients is a plus
Did a take out. We had two vegetarian sandwiches, both were delicious. A little too much bread, but I think it’s just me, it might just be fine. Chips are great.

Tasty but limited menu. Prices are higher since ingredients are either conscientious (non-gmo etc.) or imported (like the international chocolate wall). Staff is really great and keeps me coming back.
Love these sandwiches
such fresh and delicious sandwiches
Yummy I got pesto Wisconsin sandwich. I love the side of almonds option rather than chips
Great Quinoa Stew!
Good food and great service!
My favorite River North Sandwich place
good food but a bit overpriced IMO
Great quick healthy lunch.
Great place - organic food
Great sandwiches, small portions.
Very different than the other sandwich places, food was very good, quality was very good.
Decent and trendy lunch option. Slightly expensive, but at least you walk away feeling healthy.
Everyt Hong was great  would recommend this place for surr!
Fresh, delicious! But who serves espresso in tall paper cups?!
Unique sandwiches made with quality ingredients. It's a bit on the high side for cost, but that's what you get in this area of town.
Fresh ingredients. l appreciate that they label vegan options - but I wish there were more of them. Lots of gourmet chocolates.
Very fresh ingredients and very good veggie options. It is on the pricier side. Service is great

Hannah's Bretzel is my favorite place to grab a sandwich downtown-- the ingredients are always top notch, and the combinations are delicious! The food is delicious & healthy, so I enjoy eating it, and feel great afterwards, too.
$11 for a tiny sandwich. Taste's good but not a great value.
I ordered Works breakfast egg sandwich with pretzel bread. It was so delicious.

I really like the sandwiches here. You get clean, organic did that tastes delicious. I love the ingredients like white truffle goat cheese and caramelized onions. The gluten free bread was dense and dry, but everything else was on point.
I absolutely love their safe devices especially the sirloin. Additionally their chips as their side is also a delicious treat. Chocolate bar from an exotic place to top off a great meal.
Great sandwiches
Food was delicious.  Service was friendly.  Not inexpensive.
Great sandwiches! Too bad they're smaller now than they used to be

If only they served the cauliflower soup everyday! It's the best thing on the menu.  Lots of fun different chocolates, along with sandwiches and salads. Everything has been great.  Gluten free bread is fine, but definitely not the best out there.
Anyone who does not give this 6/5 stars is nuts. Too notch everything! We come for 45 mile to eat here.
Very tasty, but also was crazy busy when I went. A bit expensive, but seemed worth the cost

A consistently superior lunch option in the city. Organic and tasty sandwiches, great soups and decent salads. Artisan chocolates galore. Home baked cookies also. This place appeals to a healthy green crowd for sure as they are concerned about the packaging details and recycling. It can get very crowded at lunchtime but for carryout the line moves quickly.

The best gourmet sandwich place I have found.  Serrano ham, aged dried beef, etc. are sliced paper thin while you watch, and put together with homemade bread rolls, artisan cheeses, and other toppings.  No iceberg lettuce here!   Samdwiches are small and very expensive sandwiches though.
Tasty and high quality sandwiches made to order
Very quick and efficient team during lunch
Pricey but good.  Quality is top shelf, but you pay for it.  Reminds me of aces in Europe.  $12 for sandwich is rather high.
Pretzel rolls!

First time here tried something new to me the turkey and farmhouse cheddar with the apples on it was not expecting it to taste so good!!!!!!! 10/10 highly recommend it to everyone and they even have gluten free options. And to top it all off it's all organic

I really love the quality of food at Hannah's.  The staff are kind and hard-working.  Only two suggestions for improvement:  1. bring back the old bacon - the quality was far superior to what has been used the past couple of years; and 2. include a special sandwich of the day or week to provide some additional variety for those of us that a very frequent customers.  The tomato and cauliflower soups are truly fantastic.
Consistent quality with good options. A little expensive for how much food you get.

Love these sandwiches!  Most are made with a combination of flavors that you do not have at home. My favorite sandwich is the procuitto with machego cheese and fig spread.  They also have an AMAZING selection of chocolate.
Tasty lunch spot with pretzel bread.
Fast casual sandwich spot with emphasis on pretzel bread.

The sandwiches are delicious and feature a wide range of healthy ingredients. For those a bit less health-conscious, there is a wide assortment of domestic and foreign chocolates available while you wait in line for your sandwich.
Love their Power Breakfast Bowl.

An amazing place. I would recommend it for breakfast, lunch, or maybe an early dinner. The place is very sanitary and has good furniture and decor which I really like a lot. The outside area is very nice and is a good place to eat your food. The owner is very friendly and treats his workers like family. i think you should stop whatever you are doing and try this great restaurant out.
If you like sandwiches with A LOT of flavor, get the Sergio's Special. Other sandwiches are also flavorful. My only complaint is price.
Can only speak for their breakfast, but their Bacon and Cheese or Works breakfast sandwich on Bretzel is amazing. Definitely on the smaller (and pricier) side, but it is delicious.
Delicious. Get the Sergio Special with fresh sliced ham, chutney, and jalapeños on a pretzel roll! This location has a nice outdoor seating area.

I had ordered two Ella's salads today for lunch, one for myself and one for a co-worker. One of the two was to have no cheese or tomatoes. When I got back to the office, I looked and one salad was basically plain, the other had some beans on it. I brought both of them back and was reassured they are correct. I am looking at my salad which was to have everything on it, there is no mozzarella, no roasted tomatoes and no cashews. Very poor and disappointing! Never again, worst salad in the Loop.
Good food but the owner is a douchebag n treats his employees like shot. Otherwards decent lunch menu
You get a portion of meat that is 2 see through slices. What a rip off. Have fun eating a bun with lettuce and tomatoes for $12.
Love the sandwiches , my favourite is the one with apple, brie and caramelized onions
Great fresh food. Unique ingredients. Nice vibe inside.
Vegetable Bomb is the bomb.  An awesome, semi-organic place with spacious and comfortable seating. The Vegetable Bomb I ordered, while pricey, was delicious.
Don't order the gluten free roll. Crumbly, dry, inedible.

Avoid this place. Their menu states "call us for a catering or pickup order" yet, when we called to place an order for pickup, they told us that we would need to just come in, that we could not place an order for pickup. If I wanted to wait in a 45 minute line, I would not have called about a pickup order in the first place! Don't advertise what you do not offer.
unique and great tasting!
Sirloin and gruyere. Enough said. :)

The service depends on who you get behind the counter. My wife got someone who was really quick but I got a guy who just wanted to talk to another co-worker while making my sandwich. It took the guy, 15 minutes to make mine when it took my wife 5. We both got, "The Works" sandwiches, and man were those delicious! I would still recommend this place in heart beat.

Stopped in here for lunch while visiting the Downtown area.  I had a "club" on a pretzel bread bun. It was quite amazing. The bacon was tasty and crispy, the ham was very good and the mustard was just spicy enough to enhance the flavor of the rest of the ingredients.  If you're in the area, stop by for lunch. I'm sure you will enjoy it.

Nowadays, pretzel bread has been increasing in sales. I think it would be awesome to incorporate this new bread into more resturants. Pretzels are very salty and as humans, we require high salt intake.

With amazing pretzel-bread sandwiches at unbeatable prices, this restaurant by far surpasses others in bang-for-your-buck type return. Almost always offering specials, there is almost never a lunch where it's not worth going and trying something new. My wife loves it, and it's becoming a favorite of mine, too.
Sandwiches are good but small...like barely 7 inches small
i didn't really like it. the bread was much too tough. eh.
This is a great stop for lunch near the loop.  The chocolate selection is ridiculous and the sandwiches are a great healthy choice.  Great atmosphere inside and out.
Great food and fast service even when it's the lunch rush hour. Pretzel buns are the best and would recommend those. Favorite sandwhich is the Turkey and Farmhouse Cheddar.
Delicious pretzel bread thats always fresh!
The pretzel bread was great and I loved the fresh ingrediants. The service was also very good and they have good sized portions
Good but I've had better
I love anything on a pretzel bun.  This is a good choice to have a good sandwhich option for lunch.  Interesting choices, I like the turkey and brie.

Delicious pretzel sandwiches made with fresh ingredients. My favorite is the farmhouse turkey and cheddar, but every sandwich I've had here has been excellent. Each sandwich comes with your choice of a healthy side, so Hannah's makes the perfect work lunch break.
Yum! Was great
Always amazing for lunches. The Apple Brei sandwich is the best but the sirlon is always great.  Try the soy nuts instead of chips.
One of the great places to get those cravings! Great pretzels and drinks!
It's a good place for lunch with friends, healthy, not for business lunches.
The sandwich here are great they are huge and plentiful! The prices are good and fair. The service is excellent!
great and fun place for a snack
Really tasty sandwiches. Kind of a french style appeal. Only complaint is it is too expensive.

This location is right where I get off the bus, so it makes for an easy breakfast pick up. They have great choices for breakfast sandwiches, made with organic eggs.  I like the egg, vegetable and cheese, the bacon egg & cheese (made with nitrate free bacon!) and the goat cheese whit white truffle oil. I've also order lunch catering from this location and they always do a great job. The Thanksgiving 365 baguette is always a fan favorite during our meetings.

Love these sandwiches.  They are a great 'step-up' from a subway or a Jimmy Johns.  They also offer a great Chocolate selection to which I have not seen in any other resturant or supermarket.  The atmosphere is great, they have a pretty unique style and great color palatte for their decorations.

Love this place. Great organic options. I grab coffees there about every morning on my way to work, but the real treat are their sandwiches at lunch! Wish it wasn't always so hot in there though. It's hard to walk in there in the morning after a heated walk into work.
Overpriced and a bit tasteless. But hey, mostly organic, so that's something.
Delicious food, all organic, and reliably fast. Oh, and a crazy wall of organic sweets. Need I say more?
Small location, but they move fast. Many organic sandwich choices. The chocolate selection is plenty and rare, so definitely browse as you wait in line.
